The paper deals with algorithms for computing triangular decompositions of parametric polynomial systems, which are commonly used in computer algebra and symbolic computation. The paper also mentions the RegularChains library in Maple, which is a well-known tool for solving polynomial systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.SC (Symbolic Computation), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also discusses the division of the parametric space into sub-spaces, which suggests a connection to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science).
